U.S. House of Representatives Rejects Rescue Plan
The first chamber of the US Congress has narrowly failed the rescue plan of the financial markets heavy of 700 billion dollars.
The Dow Jones tumbled into the abyss.
With 227 votes to 206, the U.S. House of Representatives rejected the government’s bailout of financial markets.
Despite all the calls from U.S. President George W. Bush and politicians at the helm of both parties, the program that was supposed to stem the chaos of the financial markets did not win a majority.
